podman uses the content of `profile.json`.  The content in `profile.json` is parsed by Podmand and converted to a configuration usable by the OCI runtime.

We would still need to pass the plugins though (or configure them in `containers.conf`).

@haircommander would it be possible with `conmon-rs` to load `.so` files so we can support seccomp plugins as well?
